article.headline: Utah State 92, Drake 74
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll scored 24 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Utah State defeated Drake 92-74 Saturday in the semifinals of the BP Top of the World Classic. The Aggies (2-1) bolted to a 12-0 lead before Drake got on the board with a pair of free throws by Ajay Calvin. Carroll sank his first four 3-point attempts and Utah State led 56-31 at halftime behind 72 percent shooting from the field. In the second half, Drake closed to 85-69 with 4:48 remaining but could get no closer. Utah State finished 35-for-57, or 61 percent, from the field, including a perfect night by Steve DuCharme, who hit all 10 of his shots and two free throws for 22 points. Drake (1-1) shot 46 percent from the field but struggled at the free throw line, shooting just 20-for-37. Calvin scored 23 points for the Bulldogs. Klayton Korver pulled down five rebounds. Utah State faces Weber State on Sunday for the championship. Drake faces Troy for third place.
